Black Friday is the biggest shopping day on the calendar, with a growing list of South African retailers offering greatly reduced prices on a range of products. While Black Friday is set to fall on 29 November 2019, deals will likely extend to the week leading up to, and beyond the official day. Online retailers are also expected to offer a number of specials on ‘Cyber Monday’, which falls on 2 December in 2019. Below BusinessTech has compiled a list of stores which have confirmed that they will be offering Black Friday deals on and around the day. This list will be updated as more stores confirm their participation. Bidorbuy.co.za <img class="aligncenter wp-image-142119" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bidorbuy-icon-logo.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bidorbuy-icon-logo.jpg 600w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Bidorbuy-icon-logo-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Builders <img class="size-full wp-image-210639 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Builders.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Builders.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Builders-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Cell C <img class="size-full wp-image-302352 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cell-C-pin-drop.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cell-C-pin-drop.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Cell-C-pin-drop-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: